Ladysmith Black Mambazo has done it again. The popular music group bagged its fifth Grammy Award on Sunday. “Shaka Zulu revisted: 30th Anniversary Celebration” took the Best World Music Album for the South Africans. The 60th Annual Grammys were held at Madison Square Garden, New York City on 28 January. The group has been nominated 19 times in the past by the Recording Academy that administers the top prizes in US music. They were also nominated on Sunday for Children’s Album but did not win. Arts and Culture Minister Nathi Mthethwa offered his congratulations to the group on winning their award.